                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-257-victim2296 t18230910-257-viclabel1378"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18230910-257-crimeloc1379">Bull's-head-court, Great Peter-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-257-crimeloc1379" type="placeName" value="Bull's-head-court, Great Peter-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-257-crimeloc1379" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-257-off1376 t18230910-257-crimeloc1379"></join>. The prisoner lived two doors off, and worked with me. I had not seen these boots for a month, but missed the shoes on the 4th. The money was marked, and was taken from the till. On Sunday, the 12th, he was taken up, and I charged him with taking 1 s. 6 d. from the till. He immediately threw it back on the shelf, and said it was only 1 s. 6 d. I had been looking through a hole, and saw him leave his seat, and heard the till unlocked. He was the only person in the room. His wife gave me a duplicate.</p>
               <p>
            
